      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; analyst qualification documented.",
      "rationale": "Formal use error assessment not required at MRL 2. Lead analyst holds PhD in computational fluid dynamics with 8 years rotary blood pump simulation experience. Peer review of simulation setup performed by independent senior analyst. Scoped out per MRL 2 assessment table."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Governing equations and constitutive submodels documented and justified; known simplifications identified with qualitative impact assessment.",
      "rationale": "Steady-state Reynolds-averaged Navier-Stokes (RANS) with SST k-omega turbulence closure selected based on published benchmark performance for rotary blood pumps (Hariharan et al., Fraser et al.). Power-law hemolysis accumulation model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger) documented. Newtonian blood viscosity (mu = 0.0035 Pa·s) adopted; non-Newtonian Carreau-Yasuda rheology present in the physical system is excluded. Justification: at CPB operating shear rates (>100 s-1 in primary flow path) Newtonian approximation introduces <5% viscosity error per published rheology data. Sensitivity to this assumption was noted informally in the model development log but no formal sensitivity analysis was conducted and no SensitivityAnalysis artifact is linked to this package. Gradation 2 requirement considered met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
