    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet required levels for MRL 2. Six factors scoped out per MRL 2 assessment table. Validation evidence demonstrates NIH prediction error within ±15% across the CPB operating envelope with GCI < 5%. The Newtonian blood rheology simplification is acknowledged; informal sensitivity review during model development indicated negligible impact at dominant high-shear operating conditions. The credibility team concludes the evidence package is sufficient to support the COU decision at Medium assurance level. The relative hemolysis index RH < 1 acceptance criterion is met for all evaluated operating points.",
